![](/roboeyes.jpeg)

We put the robo into roboadvisors for investment advice - and guess what
happened? Its ability to maintain vs. avoid eyecontact had a similar effect on
trust when compared to a human advisor.

Read more about it at [NIM.org, my former
employer](https://www.nim.org/en/research/projects-overview/detail-research-project/how-artificial-attention-shapes-human-intention).

Simulating hundreds of virtual online meetings in parallel brought our server
to its limits and sparked the creation of [Zap](/projects/zap).

